modules.description: Checks equality of error instances and formats them for human-readable output. Works with a custom error type representing distinct error conditions. Used to compare error states during validation and to log detailed error messages in diagnostic contexts.

Provides functions to create and compare type identifiers, enabling type equality checks between opaque types. Works with the Type_id.t data type, which serves as a unique reference for type identities. Used to verify type equivalence for safe casting and proof construction in type-safe transformations.

Provides functions to compare error instances and generate human-readable representations for a custom error type. Supports validation workflows by enabling precise error state comparisons and detailed logging. Operations include equality checks and formatting, allowing developers to track and report errors effectively. For example, it can determine if two validation failures stem from the same condition or format a complex error for user display.
